ge\n  |votes      = 280,235\n  |percentage = 100.00\n}}\n{{Election box hold with party link without swing\n  |winner     = Republican Party (United States)\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==Personal life==\nStutzman and his wife, Christy, have two sons, Payton and Preston.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|35em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://stutzman.house.gov/ Congressman Marlin Stutzman] official U.S. House website\n* [http://www.gomarlin.com/ Marlin Stutzman for Congress]\n* {{C-SPAN|marlinastutzman}}\n* {{Dmoz|Regional/North_America/United_States/Indiana/Government/Federal/US_House_of_Representatives/Marlin_Stutzman_%5BR-3%5D}}\n{{CongLinks | congbio = S001188 | ballot = Marlin_Stutzman | nndb = 035/000266234 | votesmart = 34230 | govtrack = 412392 | opencong = 412392 | rollcall = 31073 | politifact = | fec = S0IN00095 | opensecrets = N00030891 | assets = marlin-stutzman | legistorm = 2752/Rep_Marlin_Stutzman_IN.html | followthemoney = 5023 | ontheissues = IN/Marlin_Stutzman.htm | congress = marlin-stutzman/1981 | worldcat = | c-span = marlinstutzman | imdb = | bloomberg = | nyt = | washpo = gIQANwHaKP }}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-par|us-hs}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Mark Souder]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Member of the [[List of United States Representatives from Indiana|U.S. House of Representatives]]<br>from [[Indiana's 3rd congressional district]]|years=2010\u2013present}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Jim Banks]]<br>{{small|Elect}}}}\n|-\n{{s-prec|usa}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Tom Reed (politician)|Tom Reed]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Seniority in the United States House of Representatives|United States Representatives by seniority]]|years=223rd}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Mike Fitzpatrick]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{IN-FedRep}}\n{{USHouseCurrent}}\n{{IndianaUSRepresentatives}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Stutzman, Marlin}}\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Farmers from Indiana]]\n[[Category:Indiana Republicans]]\n[[Category:Indiana State Senators]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Members of the Indiana House of Representa